Message.MsgText: ADMR0105E=ADMR0105E: The system is unable to write document {0}: {1}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ADMR0014W=ADMR0014W: The temporary directory {0} is not valid. The default location is used instead.
Message.Explanation: If the temporary directory is explicitly set, it must be an accessible directory that is located outside of the repository root directory.
Message.UserResponse: Use the default location or choose an accessible location outside of the configuration repository directory tree.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0114W=ADMR0114W: The system is overwriting document {0} by request.
Message.Explanation: A document in the repository was updated and one or more previous updates to the document are overwritten. These actions are performed at the request of the caller.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required, but be aware that overwriting configuration documents can cause inconsistencies in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0024E=ADMR0024E: User {0} does not have the required role to access {1} document(s).
Message.Explanation: Access to the document(s) previously identified by message ADMR0023E was denied to the indicated user.
Message.UserResponse: Grant the user the correct role to access the document.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0104E=ADMR0104E: The system is unable to read document {0}: {1}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ADMR0013W=ADMR0013W: The backup directory {0} is not valid. The default location is used instead.
Message.Explanation: If the backup directory is explicitly set, it must be an accessible directory that is located outside of the repository root directory.
Message.UserResponse: Use the default location or choose an accessible location outside of the configuration repository directory tree.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0023E=ADMR0023E: User {0} does not have the required role for {1} access to document {2}.
Message.Explanation: Access to the indicated document requires the user to have the required role (either read or update).
Message.UserResponse: Grant the user the correct role to access the document.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0019I=ADMR0019I: The temporary directory of the configuration repository is {0}.

Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0113E=ADMR0113E: The system is unable to delete document {0} after a failure: {1}
Message.Explanation: While recovering from an error, the configuration repository was unable to delete a newly created document.
Message.UserResponse: Delete the indicated document, if it is present after the process stops.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0009I=ADMR0009I: Document {0} is created.
Message.Explanation: A document is created.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0022W=ADMR0022W: The document overwrite feature may not be disabled in the node agent process.
Message.Explanation: The product set the allowConfigOverwrites system property to false for the node agent process because the document overwrite feature cannot be disabled in the node agent process.
Message.UserResponse: No action is necessary. However, to avoid seeing this message remove the node agent setting for allowConfigOverwrites system property.

Message.MsgText: ADMR0025I=ADMR0025I: The following files have been deleted from the configuration repository temporary file area because they are older than {0} minutes: {1}
Message.Explanation: Files older than a certain age are periodically cleaned out from the configuration repository temporary file area. This operation is normal.
Message.UserResponse: No action is necessary. To change the frequency with which files are cleaned up, set the com.ibm.ws.management.repository.tempFileSweepIntervalMinutes Java system property. To change the age after which files are deleted, set the com.ibm.ws.management.repository.tempFileKeepTimeMinutes Java system property.
